Zidane is Real's best scout - as well as being a terrific coach, Zidane has also proven himself as a renowned scout. His ability to pick out top talents shows that he could easily be Real's sporting director, and his respect in the game makes it tough to say no to him. [<br />
@Marca<br />
]<br />
<br />
Zidane's first major pick was Franck Ribery back in 04, when he was playing for Madrid, noticed the skillful winger at Metz. &quot;He will be one of the best players in France,&quot; he said of the then 20-year-old Ribery. He even suggested Real to sign him but it was too late. [<br />
@Marca<br />
]

Due to his adoration in France, Zidane is now fundamental in Real Madrid's hopes of landing Kylian Mbappe from PSG. Mbappe himself has frequently mentioned his admiration for Zidane If Real end up landing the PSG star, it could go down as Zidane's greatest scalp yet. [<br />
@Marca<br />
]

Eden Hazard has been putting in extra hours of his own accord to get back to full fitness as quickly as possible - he aims to feature in the Madrid derby and be at his absolute best vs Man City. [<br />
@diarioas<br />
]

At Zorrilla tomorrow - RM will be presented with an opportunity to become a sole league leader for the first time in 100 days. The last time Real had this opportunity was back at Son Moix where they were beaten by Mallorca. But since that game Madrid have been unbeaten. [<br />
@Marca<br />
]

Eden Hazard is very optimistic ahead of the Madrid derby, his recovery is going very well. [<br />
@diarioas<br />
]

Real Valladolid have asked Real Madrid to loan them Reinier Jesus for the remainder of the season. [<br />
@globoesportecom<br />
 - <br />
@Pucela_Fichajes<br />
]

Madrid dressing room was completely repulsive to the idea of Mourinho becoming their next coach when things weren't going well at the start of the season with Zidane. [<br />
@jpedrerol<br />
]

Real Madrid and Bayern Munich face a struggle to compete with Premier League giants because of the financial muscle of top English clubs, admits Karl-Heinz Rummenigge. [<br />
@diarioas<br />
]<br />
<br />
Karl-Heinz Rummenigge: &quot;I think Florentino P&eacute;rez's problem is the Premier League, because it receives three times more money from domestic TV stations than all of us. No matter if it's Spain, Germany, France etc.&quot;<br />
<br />
Karl-Heinz Rummenigge: &quot;With Real Madrid - Florentino Perez belongs to the world's most prominent club, because it's the most successful one and you have to admit it is also incredibly strong in terms of star power.&quot;

Eden Hazard could be called up for the Madrid derby and take a place on the bench. [<br />
@deportescope<br />
]<br />
<br />
2-months and 3-days later, Hazard was finally able to put his boots on and work at almost the same pace as the rest of the squad. <br />
<br />
Eden completed the entire session and was seen working with the ball and playing in the various small-sided matches organised by Zidane. [<br />
@Marca<br />
]

Luka Jovic is still disconnected from his team mates - he touched the ball only 14 times (Areola touched the ball 34 times) and was able to make only 7 passes in 73 minutes last night. So far this season he has scored only 1 goal in 748 minutes. [<br />
@diarioas<br />
]

Luka Jovic: &quot;I'm not happy with the season I'm having, at least until now. First because I can be better. Sometimes on YouTube I see videos of me last year and I ask myself 'what happened?'&quot;<br />
<br />
Luka Jovic: &quot;The pressure at Real Madrid is huge, even more so if you're only 21 and they payed 60m-euros for you. I have fought until now without success. But hope the situation changes.&quot;

